index b7f845377..000000000
--- a/.changeset/eval-trace-loader-chat-session-guard.md
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,7 +0,0 @@
----
-"@mcpjam/inspector": patch
----
-
-evals: load trace via `chatSessionId` when the legacy `blob` is absent.
-
-After the eval→chatSessions unification dropped the legacy blob writer, new iterations are created with `chatSessionId` set and `blob` unset. `useEvalTraceBlob`'s pre-roundtrip guard still required `iteration.blob`, so the backend action was never called and the trace surface rendered "No trace data is available for this run" while tokens/tool counts populated normally. The hook now gates on either source and re-fires when `chatSessionId` resolves.
diff --git a/.changeset/stage5-step3-sdk-reporter.md b/.changeset/stage5-step3-sdk-reporter.md
deleted file mode 100644
index 47609b7b8..000000000
--- a/.changeset/stage5-step3-sdk-reporter.md
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,7 +0,0 @@
----
-"@mcpjam/sdk": minor
----
-
-eval reporter: send {hostConfig, hostConfigHash} on /sdk/v1/evals/* when backend advertises `evalsHostConfig` (Stage 5 Step 3).
-
-Reporter probes `GET /sdk/v1/info` lazily (cached per baseUrl, fail-safe to "no capability"). When backend supports it AND iteration host snapshots are homogeneous, sends a normalized + content-hashed host config alongside results. Source order: `iteration.hostSnapshot` → `executor.getHostSnapshot?.()` → `MCPJamReportingConfig.host`. Heterogeneous per-iteration snapshots omit the run-level field (per-iteration wire support is a later stage). Old backends are unaffected.
